    "body": "<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\r\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\n* **New Features**\r\n  * Enabled multi stream MLA/MoE for DeepSeekR1 model. \r\n  * Enabled symm_mem AllGather which is faster than NCCL allgather \r\n  * Enabled linear ops to use DeepGemm (b projections on MLA) on Blackwell (SM100f) so that we can optimize out redundant typecasts (Used for MLA and MLP)\r\n  * Applied AllReduce + Add. + RMS fusion for attention \r\n  * Enabled mlir eltwise fusion and applied required fixes\r\n  * Update DeepSeek-R1 config\r\n  * As a result, achieving 85% of pytorch backend's performance for 1K/1K/conc 256 case in terms of OTPS\r\n\r\n## Test Coverage\r\n \r\n- AllGather strategies: tests/unittest/_torch/multi_gpu/test_allgather.py, tests/unittest/_torch/auto_deploy/multigpu/transformations/test_ad_dist_strategies.py::test_allgather_strategy_propagation\r\n- Deepgemm: tests/unittest/auto_deploy/singlegpu/transformations/library/test_finegrained_fp8_swiglu.py::test_finegrained_fp8_swiglu_deepgem_scale_layout \r\n:- AllReduce + Add + RMS : tests/unittest/auto_deploy/multigpu/transformations/library/test_allreduce_residual_rmsnorm_fusion.py\r\n- MLIR eltwise fusion : tests/unittest/auto_deploy/singlegpu/mlir/test_elementwise_fusion_e2e.py\r\n\r\n## PR Checklist\r\n\r\nPlease review the following before submitting your PR:\r\n- PR description clearly explains what and why. If using CodeRabbit's summary, please make sure it makes sense.\r\n- PR Follows [TRT-LLM CODING GUIDELINES](https://github.com/NVIDIA/TensorRT-LLM/blob/main/CODING_GUIDELINES.md) to the best of your knowledge.\r\n- Test cases are provided for new code paths (see [test instructions](https://github.com/NVIDIA/TensorRT-LLM/tree/main/tests#1-how-does-the-ci-work))\r\n- Any new dependencies have been scanned for license and vulnerabilities\r\n- [CODEOWNERS](https://github.com/NVIDIA/TensorRT-LLM/blob/main/.github/CODEOWNERS) updated if ownership changes\r\n- Documentation updated as needed\r\n- Update [tava architecture diagram](https://github.com/NVIDIA/TensorRT-LLM/blob/main/.github/tava_architecture_diagram.md) if there is a significant design change in PR.\r\n- The reviewers assigned automatically/manually are appropriate for the PR.\r\n\r\n\r\n- [x] Please check this after reviewing the above items as appropriate for this PR.\r\n\r\n## GitHub Bot Help\r\n\r\nTo see a list of available CI bot commands, please comment `/bot help`.\r\n",
